1
00:01:35,200 --> 00:01:36,120
What did you want to see me about?

2
00:01:39,160 --> 00:01:41,720
Xiao Min, please reason with Xuan Yan.

3
00:01:42,240 --> 00:01:44,000
Get him to go to the chairman,

4
00:01:44,000 --> 00:01:45,720
swallow his pride, and apologize.

5
00:01:45,760 --> 00:01:47,440
I believe the chairman would be willing

6
00:01:47,440 --> 00:01:49,360
to sit down and talk it out with him.

7
00:01:49,760 --> 00:01:50,480
This partnership,

8
00:01:50,480 --> 00:01:53,120
we can still keep it going.

9
00:01:53,440 --> 00:01:55,320
Neither side should burn all the bridges.

10
00:01:55,320 --> 00:01:56,360
Alright?

11
00:01:58,160 --> 00:01:58,920
This is the only thing

12
00:01:58,920 --> 00:02:01,280
I can still do for Xuan Yan right now.

13
00:02:02,480 --> 00:02:04,960
If not today, then tomorrow at the latest.

14
00:02:05,080 --> 00:02:07,560
The chairman could take action any moment.

15
00:02:07,560 --> 00:02:08,880
Once things turn ugly,

16
00:02:08,880 --> 00:02:10,479
there'll be no room left to maneuver.

17
00:02:10,479 --> 00:02:11,200
Do you understand?

18
00:02:11,200 --> 00:02:12,960
Is your chairman really that impressive?

19
00:02:13,800 --> 00:02:15,280
Did he put you under a spell?

20
00:02:15,880 --> 00:02:17,200
Can't you live without him?

21
00:02:17,240 --> 00:02:18,480
The rotten things Zheng Guohui has done,

22
00:02:18,480 --> 00:02:19,480
don't you know about them?

23
00:02:20,160 --> 00:02:22,320
Xin Ran, look at yourself right now.

24
00:02:22,400 --> 00:02:24,280
You're a capable woman.

25
00:02:24,840 --> 00:02:25,960
The way you'd normally stride around

26
00:02:25,960 --> 00:02:27,560
in those high heels, where did that go?

27
00:02:28,520 --> 00:02:30,240
I really don't like who you are right now.

28
00:02:32,200 --> 00:02:33,920
Xiao Min, you don't understand me.

29
00:02:36,360 --> 00:02:37,360
I have no choice.

30
00:02:37,560 --> 00:02:38,720
Is it that you have no choice,

31
00:02:38,720 --> 00:02:41,080
or you can't let go of Dayazhai's GM seat?

32
00:02:46,880 --> 00:02:48,960
Xiao Min, I'm a divorced woman.

33
00:02:49,480 --> 00:02:51,320
My family is broken.

34
00:02:51,680 --> 00:02:53,360
I have no degree, no connections.

35
00:02:53,360 --> 00:02:55,120
I can't even keep my own child

36
00:02:55,360 --> 00:02:57,000
by my side.

37
00:02:58,080 --> 00:02:59,360
When I hit rock bottom,

38
00:03:00,680 --> 00:03:02,880
Zheng Guohui put food on my table.

39
00:03:03,280 --> 00:03:05,800
I'll owe him for the rest of my life.

40
00:03:05,800 --> 00:03:07,120
How am I supposed to choose?

41
00:03:10,800 --> 00:03:12,000
And this company,

42
00:03:12,440 --> 00:03:14,720
it took countless sleepless nights,

43
00:03:15,680 --> 00:03:17,360
it was me, Xin Ran, who built it up

44
00:03:17,360 --> 00:03:19,440
brick by brick from the ruins.

45
00:03:19,880 --> 00:03:22,680
It's the foundation of my confidence.

46
00:03:22,800 --> 00:03:24,120
Only this career

47
00:03:24,120 --> 00:03:26,360
makes me feel my life has any worth.

48
00:03:26,360 --> 00:03:28,720
Lose it, and I have nothing left.

49
00:03:28,720 --> 00:03:29,720
Do you get it?

50
00:03:31,800 --> 00:03:32,160
Xin Ran,

51
00:03:32,200 --> 00:03:34,120
you don't have to cling to this one tree.

52
00:03:40,960 --> 00:03:42,160
Come work at my factory.

53
00:03:42,760 --> 00:03:45,040
GM, chairman, take your pick.

54
00:03:45,560 --> 00:03:47,280
My factory may be a bit rustic,

55
00:03:47,320 --> 00:03:48,440
but if you're willing,

56
00:03:48,560 --> 00:03:49,360
let's transform it together.

57
00:03:49,360 --> 00:03:49,960
Alright?

58
00:03:50,240 --> 00:03:51,360
Xiao Min...

59
00:03:55,320 --> 00:03:57,280
I'm not as good as you think I am.

60
00:04:00,360 --> 00:04:01,120
I don't care.

61
00:04:10,320 --> 00:04:11,480
You don't care?

62
00:04:12,120 --> 00:04:14,200
You... you don't care, but I do.

63
00:04:14,720 --> 00:04:17,200
You're the man who'd hold up the sky

64
00:04:17,200 --> 00:04:19,519
on your own shoulders if it fell on me.

65
00:04:20,640 --> 00:04:22,800
But now I'm Peach Blossom Town's sinner.

66
00:04:23,520 --> 00:04:25,400
If I joined your factory right now,

67
00:04:25,400 --> 00:04:27,080
what would people think of you?

68
00:04:27,360 --> 00:04:28,480
I'm telling you, Xiao Min,

69
00:04:28,480 --> 00:04:31,160
I'd be too ashamed to face anyone.

70
00:04:35,200 --> 00:04:36,360
Take my advice.

71
00:04:37,880 --> 00:04:39,080
Go and talk some sense into Xuan Yan.

72
00:04:40,760 --> 00:04:42,200
He can't win this lawsuit.

73
00:04:43,200 --> 00:04:44,040
When it's all over,

74
00:04:45,080 --> 00:04:47,160
Peach Blossom Town's Xuan paper industry

75
00:04:47,520 --> 00:04:49,360
won't be able to survive that outcome.

76
00:04:49,880 --> 00:04:52,360
And I'd have no face to stay here.

77
00:04:55,080 --> 00:04:56,200
I'm begging you.

78
00:04:57,960 --> 00:04:58,760
Xin Ran.

79
00:04:59,520 --> 00:05:00,120
Xin Ran!

80
00:05:35,720 --> 00:05:36,680
Secretary Peng.

81
00:05:44,680 --> 00:05:47,600
What's wrong? Still hung up on it?

82
00:05:50,360 --> 00:05:51,520
I just feel...

83
00:05:52,560 --> 00:05:54,280
I'm responsible for this whole thing.

84
00:05:54,600 --> 00:05:56,280
If I hadn't pushed Xuan Yan and Xin Ran

85
00:05:56,280 --> 00:05:57,640
so hard,

86
00:05:58,520 --> 00:06:00,920
he wouldn't have rushed the Cooperative.

87
00:06:02,120 --> 00:06:04,000
He was somewhat influenced by me.

88
00:06:04,520 --> 00:06:06,120
If I'd been more patient

89
00:06:07,080 --> 00:06:09,840
and urged Xuan Yan to talk to Dayazhai more,

90
00:06:10,120 --> 00:06:11,680
maybe things wouldn't have escalated

91
00:06:11,680 --> 00:06:12,800
to where they are now.

92
00:06:13,120 --> 00:06:15,680
As the government, we must be mindful of

93
00:06:15,680 --> 00:06:17,680
our role, our role, our role.

94
00:06:17,680 --> 00:06:20,160
Do our job of supporting and guiding.

95
00:06:20,240 --> 00:06:21,800
We're not here to fix everything.

96
00:06:22,000 --> 00:06:24,240
We can't solve every single problem.

97
00:06:25,280 --> 00:06:25,760
Right.

98
00:06:26,520 --> 00:06:27,200
Simply put,

99
00:06:27,200 --> 00:06:30,680
many things have two sides to them.

100
00:06:31,240 --> 00:06:33,560
A lot of things you think are good

101
00:06:33,640 --> 00:06:36,240
may not turn out to be so in the end.

102
00:06:36,640 --> 00:06:39,240
And some things that seem very difficult,

103
00:06:39,240 --> 00:06:40,440
as time goes on,

104
00:06:40,720 --> 00:06:42,560
suddenly show light at the end of the tunnel.

105
00:06:43,680 --> 00:06:45,800
Take our Xuan paper market.

106
00:06:45,800 --> 00:06:46,960
These past couple of years, honestly,

107
00:06:47,000 --> 00:06:49,960
the economy is down, things are rough.

108
00:06:50,120 --> 00:06:51,800
But many of our enterprises

109
00:06:51,800 --> 00:06:54,240
are actively building their own

110
00:06:54,240 --> 00:06:55,400
internal productivity.

111
00:06:56,000 --> 00:06:57,680
Those Everlasting Red Couplets

112
00:06:57,680 --> 00:06:59,520
are a great example right now.

113
00:06:59,720 --> 00:07:01,560
And many of our entrepreneurs, like

114
00:07:01,880 --> 00:07:03,520
Fang Guangping, Ren Jiye,

115
00:07:03,520 --> 00:07:05,760
I think they've never given up

116
00:07:05,760 --> 00:07:07,520
on working hard to explore new paths.

117
00:07:08,960 --> 00:07:12,440
What should the government do right now?

118
00:07:13,320 --> 00:07:15,960
Serve, supervise, and guide.

119
00:07:15,960 --> 00:07:18,680
Not overly interfere with them.

120
00:07:18,680 --> 00:07:19,400
Right?

121
00:07:20,520 --> 00:07:21,240
Understood.

122
00:07:22,440 --> 00:07:23,440
This notebook is nice.

123
00:07:23,440 --> 00:07:24,120
Vice President Zhang.

124
00:07:24,120 --> 00:07:25,200
How many samples were made?

125
00:07:25,880 --> 00:07:27,120
15 have been made so far.

126
00:07:27,160 --> 00:07:28,120
Waiting for market feedback.

127
00:07:29,760 --> 00:07:31,120
Keep following up on your end.

128
00:07:31,440 --> 00:07:32,840
Convey our requirements to them.

129
00:07:33,160 --> 00:07:34,720
Get the feedback to me ASAP.

130
00:07:34,920 --> 00:07:36,040
Regarding product quality

131
00:07:36,040 --> 00:07:37,400
and target demographic positioning,

132
00:07:37,560 --> 00:07:39,000
make sure they're clear on it.

133
00:07:39,600 --> 00:07:41,640
Sister Xin, this doll looks good too.

134
00:07:41,640 --> 00:07:42,400
Maybe

135
00:07:42,440 --> 00:07:44,320
it could win over the children's market.

136
00:07:45,760 --> 00:07:46,560
President Zhang.

137
00:07:50,160 --> 00:07:51,440
GM Xin, busy?

138
00:07:52,520 --> 00:07:53,320
Something up?

139
00:07:55,560 --> 00:07:56,360
Secretary Li recently

140
00:07:56,360 --> 00:07:57,760
delivered the group's new contract.

141
00:07:57,760 --> 00:07:58,520
Did you read it?

142
00:07:59,320 --> 00:08:00,120
I did.

143
00:08:00,520 --> 00:08:01,800
I still need to think it over.

144
00:08:02,520 --> 00:08:03,560
Offering shares,

145
00:08:04,000 --> 00:08:05,320
and promoting you to group VP.

146
00:08:05,320 --> 00:08:07,240
Why hesitate on such good terms?

147
00:08:12,240 --> 00:08:14,000
I'm considering whether I'm up to it.

148
00:08:17,320 --> 00:08:19,240
Sure, sure, you're more than capable.

149
00:08:19,880 --> 00:08:21,440
Then let me just remind you,

150
00:08:21,640 --> 00:08:23,840
the Chairman is waiting.

151
00:08:26,320 --> 00:08:27,120
Goodbye.

152
00:08:41,760 --> 00:08:44,880
Sister Xin, we're rearing a tiger to bring disaster.

153
00:08:47,960 --> 00:08:51,440
Why don't we expose him

154
00:08:51,440 --> 00:08:52,520
for secretly selling paper trimmings?

155
00:08:55,680 --> 00:08:56,520
It won't work.

156
00:08:57,040 --> 00:08:59,160
The Chairman needs someone like him.

157
00:08:59,400 --> 00:09:01,200
He won't care about his little flaws.

158
00:09:05,240 --> 00:09:07,640
Group VP, plus shares.

159
00:09:08,600 --> 00:09:10,040
Such generous terms,

160
00:09:10,400 --> 00:09:12,240
the Chairman doesn't hand out lightly.

161
00:09:12,640 --> 00:09:14,440
Why are you still hesitating?

162
00:09:17,600 --> 00:09:18,320
Then what do you think,

163
00:09:18,320 --> 00:09:20,560
why is he giving it to me now?

164
00:09:21,680 --> 00:09:24,800
That... I really hadn't thought about.

165
00:09:26,000 --> 00:09:26,920
This contract,

166
00:09:27,360 --> 00:09:29,320
you can see it as a deal,

167
00:09:29,520 --> 00:09:30,880
or as a bribe.

168
00:09:31,960 --> 00:09:34,360
He's afraid I'll ruin his plans now.

169
00:09:35,680 --> 00:09:36,640
What plans?

170
00:09:39,680 --> 00:09:41,320
Him giving me the contract at this moment

171
00:09:41,960 --> 00:09:45,440
means the Chairman went after Xuan Yan.

172
00:09:46,320 --> 00:09:47,360
Xuan Yan.

173
00:09:55,200 --> 00:09:57,440
Xuan paper, known as the king of papers,

174
00:09:57,760 --> 00:09:59,120
since its inception,

175
00:09:59,200 --> 00:10:01,240
has carried the brush-and-ink legacy

176
00:10:01,240 --> 00:10:02,440
of Chinese culture.

177
00:10:02,960 --> 00:10:06,040
Ancients say: paper is short, love deep.

178
00:10:06,360 --> 00:10:08,600
This saying precisely pinpoints

179
00:10:08,600 --> 00:10:10,040
the pain point of our era.

180
00:10:10,040 --> 00:10:12,640
That is, how to find self-expression

181
00:10:12,640 --> 00:10:15,200
of slow living in a fast-paced age.

182
00:10:15,760 --> 00:10:17,040
Our Xuan paper Cultural Creative products

183
00:10:17,760 --> 00:10:20,560
meet today's audience's emotional needs,

184
00:10:20,560 --> 00:10:23,520
while spreading traditional Xuan paper.

185
00:10:23,520 --> 00:10:26,880
We bring Intangible Cultural Heritage

186
00:10:26,880 --> 00:10:27,520
out of museums and into daily life.

187
00:10:27,520 --> 00:10:29,560
So many VC firms showed up today.

188
00:10:29,880 --> 00:10:31,600
You're planning to snap us all up.

189
00:10:32,520 --> 00:10:34,240
The trendy toy market is booming now.

190
00:10:35,480 --> 00:10:35,880
Breaking Xuan paper's traditional uses,

191
00:10:35,880 --> 00:10:36,880
these Xuan paper Cultural Creative items

192
00:10:36,880 --> 00:10:38,000
belong to the younger generation.

193
00:10:39,120 --> 00:10:39,760
We should learn from them.

194
00:10:39,760 --> 00:10:41,400
Creating new, limitless possibilities.

195
00:10:41,440 --> 00:10:42,960
And offline sales channels

196
00:10:43,040 --> 00:10:44,640
can better help consumers

197
00:10:44,640 --> 00:10:46,240
through these national trend products,

198
00:10:46,600 --> 00:10:50,000
better trace the roots of tradition.

199
00:10:50,480 --> 00:10:53,360
While gaining personal fulfillment,

200
00:10:53,360 --> 00:10:56,120
they can also meet like-minded friends.

201
00:10:56,160 --> 00:10:58,040
Our vision turns Intangible Cultural Heritage

202
00:10:58,040 --> 00:11:00,040
from lecturing elders

203
00:11:00,040 --> 00:11:03,880
into a friend who lets you vent.

204
00:11:04,240 --> 00:11:05,040
Thank you.

205
00:11:12,520 --> 00:11:14,520
So our plan

206
00:11:14,640 --> 00:11:16,880
is to roll out our offline sales model

207
00:11:16,880 --> 00:11:19,120
across second and third-tier cities.

208
00:11:19,160 --> 00:11:20,440
Are you Mr. Xuan Yan?

209
00:11:21,840 --> 00:11:22,960
That's me. What's up?

210
00:11:22,960 --> 00:11:23,880
Hello, Mr. Xuan Yan.

211
00:11:24,280 --> 00:11:26,720
I'm a lawyer from Shensheng Law Firm.

212
00:11:29,040 --> 00:11:31,120
Retained by Mr. Zheng Guohui

213
00:11:31,120 --> 00:11:32,520
of Shenzhen Dayazhai Cultural Media Group,

214
00:11:32,520 --> 00:11:33,440
regarding the unauthorized use

215
00:11:33,440 --> 00:11:36,080
by you and Peach Blossom Town Cooperative

216
00:11:36,080 --> 00:11:38,600
of our client's product design patent,

217
00:11:38,600 --> 00:11:39,240
we have already filed a report

218
00:11:39,240 --> 00:11:42,040
with the Market Regulation Bureau

219
00:11:42,040 --> 00:11:43,000
in Xuancheng City.

220
00:11:43,640 --> 00:11:45,200
Under the relevant legal provisions,

221
00:11:45,400 --> 00:11:47,760
please immediately stop all infringement.

222
00:11:48,880 --> 00:11:49,640
Hold on.

223
00:11:49,640 --> 00:11:50,880
Xuan Yan, what's going on here?

224
00:11:51,240 --> 00:11:52,120
Infringing what?

225
00:11:52,120 --> 00:11:52,520
What's happening?

226
00:11:52,520 --> 00:11:53,440
I've already put all my money in.

227
00:11:53,440 --> 00:11:54,440
We can't stop now!

228
00:11:54,520 --> 00:11:55,360
Xuan Yan, what's going on?

229
00:11:55,360 --> 00:11:55,640
Xuan Yan!

230
00:11:55,640 --> 00:11:56,520
What's this all about?

231
00:11:57,480 --> 00:11:58,120
Something's wrong.

232
00:12:00,640 --> 00:12:01,320
Even lawyers have shown up.

233
00:12:01,320 --> 00:12:02,400
This looks pretty serious.

234
00:12:02,560 --> 00:12:03,400
What's going on?

235
00:12:09,080 --> 00:12:10,040
Can it wait a few days?

236
00:12:10,160 --> 00:12:12,360
We're suing Dayazhai for bad-faith filing.

237
00:12:12,360 --> 00:12:14,360
Let's tell everyone once we have the result.

238
00:12:14,760 --> 00:12:15,640
That's not possible.

239
00:12:15,760 --> 00:12:18,120
We've already received Dayazhai's complaint.

240
00:12:18,120 --> 00:12:19,360
As the Market Regulation Bureau,

241
00:12:19,360 --> 00:12:22,200
we must handle it by the book.

242
00:12:22,400 --> 00:12:23,600
Before we came,

243
00:12:23,600 --> 00:12:26,120
we fully considered

244
00:12:26,480 --> 00:12:27,480
the negative impact.

245
00:12:27,520 --> 00:12:30,400
That's why we asked Secretary Peng today

246
00:12:30,400 --> 00:12:32,240
to discuss this with you.

247
00:12:32,480 --> 00:12:35,600
We must handle this properly.

248
00:12:35,760 --> 00:12:36,480
Right.

249
00:12:36,520 --> 00:12:38,520
Here's the thing. Normally, we should

250
00:12:38,520 --> 00:12:40,520
have the Market Regulation Bureau comrades

251
00:12:40,520 --> 00:12:42,040
notify every household one by one.

252
00:12:42,360 --> 00:12:44,720
But considering how folks would take it,

253
00:12:45,120 --> 00:12:48,280
President Xiao, we'd like you to step in.

254
00:12:48,280 --> 00:12:50,360
That way we can keep the tension

255
00:12:50,360 --> 00:12:52,560
within a manageable range.

256
00:12:52,960 --> 00:12:54,360
I understand, Secretary Peng.

257
00:12:55,520 --> 00:12:57,400
But here's the key issue:

258
00:12:57,640 --> 00:12:59,240
This whole thing, from the start,

259
00:12:59,240 --> 00:13:00,720
was something I encouraged everyone to do.

260
00:13:00,720 --> 00:13:02,040
Everyone's enthusiasm now

261
00:13:02,040 --> 00:13:03,200
is already at its peak.

262
00:13:03,760 --> 00:13:07,040
If we suddenly say to stop, well...

263
00:13:07,960 --> 00:13:09,560
President Xiao, I'll go with you.

264
00:13:09,560 --> 00:13:11,200
If you can't say it, I will.

265
00:13:11,240 --> 00:13:12,800
No, no, no, you can't go.

266
00:13:12,800 --> 00:13:13,480
If you go,

267
00:13:13,480 --> 00:13:14,520
and everyone gets worked up,

268
00:13:14,520 --> 00:13:15,560
things will spiral out of control.

269
00:13:16,120 --> 00:13:17,120
Someone has to go.

270
00:13:17,120 --> 00:13:18,400
You can't leave it unresolved.

271
00:13:19,480 --> 00:13:20,240
Right.

272
00:13:20,760 --> 00:13:23,360
Yiran, you go with President Xiao.

273
00:13:23,520 --> 00:13:25,760
We need to show our stance too.

274
00:13:26,400 --> 00:13:27,200
Okay.

275
00:13:27,880 --> 00:13:28,760
Over three hundred thousand.

276
00:13:28,960 --> 00:13:30,560
How am I supposed to pay it back?

277
00:13:30,560 --> 00:13:32,040
Yeah, we borrowed too.

278
00:13:32,040 --> 00:13:33,160
It's all borrowed money.

279
00:13:33,520 --> 00:13:34,560
We all borrowed it.

280
00:13:34,560 --> 00:13:35,240
Same for all of us.

281
00:13:35,240 --> 00:13:36,400
We all borrowed the money.

282
00:13:36,400 --> 00:13:37,480
It's all borrowed money.

283
00:13:37,480 --> 00:13:38,600
What are we supposed to do?

284
00:13:38,600 --> 00:13:40,640
Patents were snatched behind our backs!

285
00:13:40,840 --> 00:13:42,000
What were you people even doing?

286
00:13:42,200 --> 00:13:43,040
Exactly!

287
00:13:43,040 --> 00:13:44,480
Yeah, what were you doing?

288
00:13:44,480 --> 00:13:45,880
I'm responsible for this.

289
00:13:46,160 --> 00:13:47,440
I've let you all down.

290
00:13:47,480 --> 00:13:48,760
I know you're all angry.

291
00:13:48,760 --> 00:13:50,040
So, take it all out on me.

292
00:13:50,040 --> 00:13:51,160
I'll take it, okay?

293
00:13:51,200 --> 00:13:52,960
What's the point of yelling at you?

294
00:13:53,240 --> 00:13:54,200
You just taking it,

295
00:13:54,200 --> 00:13:56,560
does that solve anything?

296
00:13:57,000 --> 00:13:57,440
Director Lin,

297
00:13:58,040 --> 00:13:58,760
this Zheng Guohui,

298
00:13:58,840 --> 00:14:00,400
what he's doing is downright despicable!

299
00:14:00,800 --> 00:14:01,760
I'm not stopping work.

300
00:14:01,760 --> 00:14:02,760
Let's see what he can do.

301
00:14:02,760 --> 00:14:04,200
Right, we can't stop.

302
00:14:04,200 --> 00:14:04,960
We won't stop.

303
00:14:04,960 --> 00:14:05,960
Absolutely won't stop.

304
00:14:05,960 --> 00:14:07,360
Right, right, we won't stop.

305
00:14:07,440 --> 00:14:08,520
How can we stop working?

306
00:14:08,520 --> 00:14:09,440
Alright, alright.

307
00:14:09,640 --> 00:14:11,800
Things aren't at their worst yet, right?

308
00:14:12,000 --> 00:14:13,040
But it's so much money.

309
00:14:13,280 --> 00:14:16,240
Xuan Yan is on his way to find a lawyer.

310
00:14:16,240 --> 00:14:18,400
We're about to officially sue Dayazhai.

311
00:14:20,600 --> 00:14:21,680
Everyone, don't worry.

312
00:14:22,000 --> 00:14:23,360
We'll do everything we can

313
00:14:23,760 --> 00:14:26,280
to take back the copyrights and patents.

314
00:14:26,520 --> 00:14:27,880
Right, we must take them back.

315
00:14:27,880 --> 00:14:28,480
We have to get them back.

316
00:14:28,480 --> 00:14:29,360
No way around it.

317
00:14:29,760 --> 00:14:31,240
Only after that can we resume work.

318
00:14:31,240 --> 00:14:32,280
If not, sue Dayazhai.

319
00:14:32,280 --> 00:14:33,160
Just sue them.

320
00:14:33,280 --> 00:14:35,200
You're anxious? I'm even more so.

321
00:14:35,400 --> 00:14:37,520
Officially, I'm the association president.

322
00:14:37,520 --> 00:14:40,000
Personally, I'm the Cooperative's major shareholder.

323
00:14:40,360 --> 00:14:41,800
But no matter how urgent,

324
00:14:41,800 --> 00:14:43,240
we can't act foolishly, right?

325
00:14:43,240 --> 00:14:44,400
Let me say it again.

326
00:14:44,400 --> 00:14:47,280
Work must halt until the lawsuit ends.

327
00:14:48,160 --> 00:14:49,000
Erhu,

328
00:14:49,440 --> 00:14:50,840
listen up, work must stop.

329
00:14:50,840 --> 00:14:52,000
If we stop, how do we eat?

330
00:14:52,000 --> 00:14:53,000
Right, how do we survive without work?

331
00:14:53,000 --> 00:14:54,600
If we don't stop, it becomes illegal.

332
00:15:07,400 --> 00:15:08,120
Wang Esq.

333
00:15:09,040 --> 00:15:10,600
These are all my design drafts.

334
00:15:10,600 --> 00:15:12,040
From the initial simple ideas

335
00:15:12,040 --> 00:15:15,840
to the finalized versions, they're all here.

336
00:15:17,200 --> 00:15:18,400
With this in hand,

337
00:15:19,280 --> 00:15:21,880
in my experience, winning is no problem.

338
00:15:23,400 --> 00:15:24,360
You're that confident?

339
00:15:26,520 --> 00:15:27,720
I wouldn't say so if I wasn't sure.

340
00:15:28,120 --> 00:15:29,480
I've been practicing for 26 years.

341
00:15:29,760 --> 00:15:31,120
Copyright and patent cases,

342
00:15:31,120 --> 00:15:32,520
I've handled hundreds, if not thousands.

343
00:15:32,800 --> 00:15:34,440
Very few have I actually lost.

344
00:15:35,200 --> 00:15:36,640
All from client referrals,

345
00:15:37,280 --> 00:15:38,480
all cases of this type.

346
00:15:40,800 --> 00:15:42,520
Seeing how well-prepared you are,

347
00:15:42,760 --> 00:15:43,880
I feel confident already.

348
00:15:44,280 --> 00:15:45,880
Never mind that you're this well-prepared,

349
00:15:46,120 --> 00:15:47,480
even if the evidence weren't sufficient,

350
00:15:48,040 --> 00:15:49,400
I'd still win it for you.

351
00:15:51,120 --> 00:15:52,360
Well, that's great to hear.

352
00:15:52,880 --> 00:15:54,040
I'll leave it in your hands, then.

353
00:15:54,720 --> 00:15:56,360
Don't worry, leave it to me.

354
00:15:59,000 --> 00:16:02,680
Wang Esq. says he's 100% certain.

355
00:16:03,800 --> 00:16:05,640
Isn't 100% certainty a good thing?

356
00:16:06,760 --> 00:16:09,360
I'm not questioning Wang Esq.'s expertise.

357
00:16:09,720 --> 00:16:10,880
I just feel that in this matter,

358
00:16:10,880 --> 00:16:12,360
if anything unexpected happens,

359
00:16:12,360 --> 00:16:13,640
the consequences would be severe.

360
00:16:13,760 --> 00:16:16,240
Why not consult a few more lawyers,

361
00:16:16,240 --> 00:16:17,520
and weigh your options?

362
00:16:18,000 --> 00:16:20,200
I visited three firms today.

363
00:16:20,360 --> 00:16:22,360
Two of them told me they weren't sure.

364
00:16:22,640 --> 00:16:24,160
Only Wang Esq. told me

365
00:16:24,160 --> 00:16:25,360
that he's 100% certain.

366
00:16:25,360 --> 00:16:26,800
So tell me, who should I choose?

367
00:16:27,680 --> 00:16:28,480
Xuan Yan,

368
00:16:28,840 --> 00:16:31,160
I've no experience with patent lawsuits.

369
00:16:31,200 --> 00:16:33,400
So I share Director Lin's concern.

370
00:16:33,400 --> 00:16:35,280
Wang Esq. says winning is guaranteed.

371
00:16:35,520 --> 00:16:36,840
He's just too confident.

372
00:16:36,840 --> 00:16:38,240
That's why we're uneasy.

373
00:16:38,840 --> 00:16:40,680
But we still respect your decision.

374
00:16:40,760 --> 00:16:41,760
You choose who to hire.

375
00:16:42,240 --> 00:16:44,000
But there's one thing you must make clear to him.

376
00:16:44,520 --> 00:16:45,800
If you go with him,

377
00:16:46,160 --> 00:16:47,880
legal fees are paid only after winning the case.

378
00:16:48,160 --> 00:16:49,000
Got it.

379
00:16:49,720 --> 00:16:52,040
I know you're all worried about me.

380
00:16:52,520 --> 00:16:53,920
But there's a saying that goes,

381
00:16:54,200 --> 00:16:56,520
Hire who you trust, trust who you hire.

382
00:16:56,800 --> 00:16:58,600
Since I've already chosen him,

383
00:16:58,600 --> 00:16:59,880
I should trust him.

384
00:17:18,480 --> 00:17:21,000
What's wrong? Still worried about me?

385
00:17:21,680 --> 00:17:22,640
Don't overthink it.

386
00:17:23,839 --> 00:17:25,520
I decided all of this myself.

387
00:17:27,760 --> 00:17:29,240
After my dad passed away,

388
00:17:30,360 --> 00:17:32,360
I never felt at home again.

389
00:17:32,920 --> 00:17:33,600
I don't even know

390
00:17:33,600 --> 00:17:36,000
when I started to realize

391
00:17:37,480 --> 00:17:39,120
that I have to rely on myself for everything,

392
00:17:40,120 --> 00:17:42,080
that only I can control my own fate.

393
00:17:42,080 --> 00:17:42,840
All these

394
00:17:44,840 --> 00:17:46,360
so-called grown-up truths.

395
00:17:48,600 --> 00:17:50,400
I've been reflecting on myself lately.

396
00:17:52,120 --> 00:17:54,000
Why is it that whenever I face a problem,

397
00:17:54,680 --> 00:17:57,400
whenever I hit a wall, I fall apart emotionally?

398
00:17:58,160 --> 00:17:59,440
Now I understand.

399
00:17:59,760 --> 00:18:01,280
I'm afraid of failing,

400
00:18:02,440 --> 00:18:05,960
of that sense of loss after failure.

401
00:18:07,680 --> 00:18:09,240
Everyone says I push myself too hard.

402
00:18:10,360 --> 00:18:11,400
I'm pushing myself desperately

403
00:18:11,400 --> 00:18:13,400
to find that sense of security.

404
00:18:17,880 --> 00:18:21,240
Life, well, it's always full of the unknown.

405
00:18:21,360 --> 00:18:23,520
But whether it's good or bad,

406
00:18:23,760 --> 00:18:25,120
success or failure,

407
00:18:26,120 --> 00:18:27,280
it's all something new.

408
00:18:28,000 --> 00:18:28,640
Right?

409
00:18:30,240 --> 00:18:30,800
Right.

410
00:18:32,040 --> 00:18:32,600
Okay.

411
00:18:36,880 --> 00:18:38,040
From now on,

412
00:18:38,760 --> 00:18:42,760
you have to learn to let everything happen.

413
00:18:43,280 --> 00:18:44,240
Know why?

414
00:18:48,080 --> 00:18:49,560
Because I'll be right here with you.

415
00:18:51,320 --> 00:18:53,600
Maybe I can't shield you from the storms,

416
00:18:54,280 --> 00:18:57,520
but I'll brave the storm right beside you.

417
00:18:57,720 --> 00:19:01,040
We'll overcome all obstacles together.

418
00:19:03,280 --> 00:19:05,320
No matter what happens, good or bad,

419
00:19:05,680 --> 00:19:06,840
we'll face it together.

420
00:19:10,280 --> 00:19:11,240
Work hard together,

421
00:19:12,160 --> 00:19:13,720
and make Xuan paper young again.

422
00:19:17,520 --> 00:19:18,800
Make Xuan paper young again.

423
00:19:24,800 --> 00:19:26,400
That lawyer Xuan Yan hired,

424
00:19:27,160 --> 00:19:28,400
maybe he's right.

425
00:19:28,400 --> 00:19:29,960
After all, he's the professional.

426
00:19:29,960 --> 00:19:31,960
I just think

427
00:19:31,960 --> 00:19:34,160
we can't underestimate Zheng Guohui.

428
00:19:34,160 --> 00:19:36,720
He's been in business for decades.

429
00:19:37,080 --> 00:19:38,160
He's no pushover.

430
00:19:40,000 --> 00:19:42,520
Now that Secretary Peng mentions it, true.

431
00:19:42,720 --> 00:19:44,400
Something that could be overturned so easily,

432
00:19:44,760 --> 00:19:45,960
would Zheng Guohui really do that?

433
00:19:46,040 --> 00:19:48,000
He's a sly old fox.

434
00:19:48,760 --> 00:19:51,200
Director Liao, don't worry too much.

435
00:19:51,240 --> 00:19:52,400
Being a bit pessimistic

436
00:19:52,520 --> 00:19:54,160
might help us make fewer mistakes.

437
00:19:54,400 --> 00:19:55,680
We've still got to stay optimistic.

438
00:19:55,760 --> 00:19:57,920
Only optimism gets us far.

439
00:20:00,760 --> 00:20:01,920
Hey, aren't you eating?

440
00:20:02,000 --> 00:20:02,800
What are you doing?

441
00:20:02,800 --> 00:20:03,560
Not hungry.

442
00:20:04,000 --> 00:20:05,080
You just said to be optimistic.

443
00:20:05,240 --> 00:20:07,200
Skipping meals is hardly optimistic.

444
00:20:08,040 --> 00:20:09,240
Don't just stand there, go get food!

445
00:20:09,240 --> 00:20:09,920
I'll get the food, I'll get it.

446
00:20:09,920 --> 00:20:10,800
I'm not hungry.

447
00:20:10,800 --> 00:20:11,480
I'll go.

448
00:20:14,760 --> 00:20:16,240
Anyway, no matter what,

449
00:20:16,240 --> 00:20:18,280
I hope Xuan Yan can face it.

450
00:20:18,320 --> 00:20:19,760
He said it himself before,

451
00:20:19,920 --> 00:20:22,000
allow everything to happen,

452
00:20:22,000 --> 00:20:23,680
allow everything to be imperfect.

453
00:20:24,000 --> 00:20:25,520
I didn't understand it back then.

454
00:20:25,640 --> 00:20:27,000
Now I do.

455
00:20:27,200 --> 00:20:28,320
Back then,

456
00:20:28,400 --> 00:20:31,200
I was just rushing to launch the Cooperative.

457
00:20:31,400 --> 00:20:35,400
The past can't be changed, but the future can still be won.

458
00:20:35,760 --> 00:20:38,000
Forget the past, look to the future.

459
00:20:38,840 --> 00:20:39,920
Go ask Xuan Yan quickly,

460
00:20:39,960 --> 00:20:42,480
when will he make my Paper Dragon Boat?

461
00:20:43,880 --> 00:20:44,640
That's true.

462
00:20:44,640 --> 00:20:46,760
The Paper Dragon Boat can't wait.

463
00:20:46,840 --> 00:20:48,240
Otherwise, our Director Liao here,

464
00:20:48,240 --> 00:20:49,360
his hair will turn white from stress.

465
00:20:51,720 --> 00:20:52,800
If the Paper Dragon Boat can't be made,

466
00:20:52,800 --> 00:20:55,160
I might as well not play Wang Lun.

467
00:20:55,160 --> 00:20:55,760
Then what would you play?

468
00:20:55,760 --> 00:20:58,520
I'll play Qu Yuan jumping into the river.

469
00:20:58,920 --> 00:21:00,080
So you'll know

470
00:21:00,520 --> 00:21:04,400
what "Even facing death, I will not yield" means.

471
00:21:06,520 --> 00:21:07,080
Here it is.

472
00:21:07,480 --> 00:21:08,200
Thanks, thanks.

473
00:21:08,400 --> 00:21:09,200
Eat up.

474
00:21:09,440 --> 00:21:12,800
Full belly, light heart, drop the burden.

475
00:21:13,280 --> 00:21:15,000
Good, take a big bite.

476
00:21:15,440 --> 00:21:16,400
That's more like it.

477
00:21:18,000 --> 00:21:19,680
Your grandfather used to say,

478
00:21:19,920 --> 00:21:23,200
A word can land you in court, and nine oxen can't pull you out.

479
00:21:23,480 --> 00:21:25,840
Meaning once you step into court,

480
00:21:26,160 --> 00:21:27,960
the outcome is unpredictable.

481
00:21:28,720 --> 00:21:32,960
So forgive whenever you can,

482
00:21:33,200 --> 00:21:35,520
and bow your head whenever you can.

483
00:21:35,560 --> 00:21:38,560
Then this whole thing will just blow over.

484
00:21:39,280 --> 00:21:40,080
Mom, look,

485
00:21:41,000 --> 00:21:43,240
Dad's got such wisdom about life now.

486
00:21:43,840 --> 00:21:44,600
Then Dad, let me ask you,

487
00:21:45,000 --> 00:21:46,480
Could you bow down to Hongxing Factory?

488
00:21:51,320 --> 00:21:53,200
Father and son, same stubborn temper.

489
00:21:54,320 --> 00:21:55,000
Xuan Yan.

490
00:21:55,680 --> 00:21:57,040
What your dad told you,

491
00:21:57,200 --> 00:21:58,760
you absolutely must remember.

492
00:21:59,240 --> 00:22:00,480
Be very careful.

493
00:22:01,160 --> 00:22:02,680
There's so much at stake.

494
00:22:03,320 --> 00:22:05,040
Don't worry, I know.

495
00:22:06,240 --> 00:22:08,800
Did the lawyer say how to fight this case?

496
00:22:09,640 --> 00:22:10,400
Well, for now,

497
00:22:10,400 --> 00:22:12,680
I've handed all of my design drafts

498
00:22:13,040 --> 00:22:14,160
over to him.

499
00:22:14,360 --> 00:22:15,280
That can prove

500
00:22:15,280 --> 00:22:18,200
my entire design process is intact.

501
00:22:18,360 --> 00:22:19,160
That's good, then.

502
00:22:19,920 --> 00:22:20,680
Let me ask you,

503
00:22:21,760 --> 00:22:23,480
that design you did,

504
00:22:24,040 --> 00:22:27,240
did it use paper I made after my back injury?

505
00:22:27,560 --> 00:22:28,480
Yes, definitely.

506
00:22:29,000 --> 00:22:30,400
Didn't I sell that earlier batch already?

507
00:22:30,400 --> 00:22:33,040
That was paper I made myself, personally.

508
00:22:34,160 --> 00:22:39,800
It has a special watermark I designed.

509
00:22:40,840 --> 00:22:44,440
The words 'Made by Xuan Yongnian.'

510
00:22:46,040 --> 00:22:47,520
Yes, yes, I remember.

511
00:22:47,560 --> 00:22:48,640
When your dad was making it,

512
00:22:48,640 --> 00:22:49,560
I even said,

513
00:22:49,560 --> 00:22:51,160
"Why bother? It's out of print."

514
00:22:51,160 --> 00:22:52,200
"You can't even sell it."

515
00:22:52,200 --> 00:22:52,760
So that's a thing.

516
00:22:52,760 --> 00:22:53,560
I get it now.

517
00:22:53,560 --> 00:22:54,840
So what that means is,

518
00:22:54,960 --> 00:22:56,400
if my design drafts

519
00:22:56,400 --> 00:22:57,960
used this batch of your paper,

520
00:22:57,960 --> 00:23:00,480
then the watermark can serve as evidence.

521
00:23:02,440 --> 00:23:02,960
Then...

522
00:23:03,960 --> 00:23:05,320
You, you go and look for it.

523
00:23:05,520 --> 00:23:06,240
Right, right, right.

524
00:23:06,240 --> 00:23:07,280
I'll go look for it right now.

525
00:23:07,320 --> 00:23:08,280
Finish your meal first.

526
00:23:08,280 --> 00:23:09,400
It's fine, it's fine, you guys eat.

527
00:23:09,400 --> 00:23:10,360
I'm heading back to check right now.

528
00:23:11,160 --> 00:23:12,000
This kid.

529
00:23:14,560 --> 00:23:16,240
You finally said something useful.

530
00:23:16,560 --> 00:23:19,240
Let's hope it works. Let's hope.

531
00:23:51,160 --> 00:23:52,840
Good thing the old man had this trick up his sleeve.

532
00:24:13,760 --> 00:24:16,640
I'd like to first offer the court a necessary explanation.

533
00:24:16,960 --> 00:24:18,920
Any design, from the initial inspiration,

534
00:24:19,400 --> 00:24:20,600
through the revision process,

535
00:24:21,200 --> 00:24:22,360
to the final finished version,

536
00:24:22,600 --> 00:24:24,640
always involves a complete design process.

537
00:24:25,560 --> 00:24:26,640
The plaintiff, Mr. Xuan Yan,

538
00:24:26,960 --> 00:24:28,920
provided the full set of design materials.

539
00:24:29,440 --> 00:24:30,560
These are my client's,

540
00:24:31,080 --> 00:24:34,040
Mr. Xuan Yan's original design drafts.

541
00:24:34,240 --> 00:24:36,680
The coherence of the design ideas in these manuscripts,

542
00:24:36,760 --> 00:24:38,320
the consistency of the design concept,

543
00:24:38,520 --> 00:24:41,120
and the sketches from the creative process

544
00:24:41,480 --> 00:24:42,480
are enough to prove

545
00:24:42,920 --> 00:24:46,240
that my client is the true rights holder.

546
00:24:46,240 --> 00:24:47,760
What I really want to point out is,

547
00:24:48,160 --> 00:24:50,400
if the disputed design manuscripts

548
00:24:50,400 --> 00:24:52,480
were truly created by the defendant's designer,

549
00:24:52,480 --> 00:24:53,280
as they claim,

550
00:24:53,280 --> 00:24:54,520
then the defendant

551
00:24:54,520 --> 00:24:57,200
should also have traces of the process.

552
00:24:57,840 --> 00:24:59,760
We also have a complete set of materials

553
00:25:00,240 --> 00:25:01,000
sufficient to prove

554
00:25:01,000 --> 00:25:02,240
that every one of our products,

555
00:25:02,280 --> 00:25:04,000
from concept, design,

556
00:25:04,000 --> 00:25:05,560
through the entire creation process,

557
00:25:06,040 --> 00:25:07,680
was independently completed by our side.

558
00:25:08,280 --> 00:25:09,720
I only ever gave them the final versions.

559
00:25:10,760 --> 00:25:11,840
Where did these materials come from?

560
00:25:12,400 --> 00:25:13,840
That bastard Zheng Guohui.

561
00:25:14,400 --> 00:25:16,920
He's schemed every angle, no scruples.

562
00:25:19,040 --> 00:25:21,400
This President Zheng is quite scheming.

563
00:25:21,400 --> 00:25:23,080
He even faked a complete set.

564
00:25:27,160 --> 00:25:27,840
Your Honor,

565
00:25:28,560 --> 00:25:31,480
the plaintiff requests our witness take the stand.

566
00:26:16,760 --> 00:26:18,520
The other side seems very well prepared.

567
00:26:18,840 --> 00:26:20,280
It'll be hard to tell true from false.

568
00:26:20,480 --> 00:26:21,480
In this situation,

569
00:26:23,040 --> 00:26:25,040
things are very unfavorable for us.

570
00:26:27,480 --> 00:26:28,080
Wang Esq.,

571
00:26:30,080 --> 00:26:32,800
should we bring up the hidden watermark now?

572
00:26:34,160 --> 00:26:34,840
Alright.

573
00:26:36,440 --> 00:26:39,520
Your Honor, we have additional evidence to submit.

574
00:26:44,400 --> 00:26:45,600
Your Honor, please take note.

575
00:26:45,800 --> 00:26:47,320
The sheet you're holding right now,

576
00:26:47,320 --> 00:26:49,840
the paper marked 'Made by Xuan Yongnian',

577
00:26:49,840 --> 00:26:51,200
and the original patent application draft

578
00:26:51,200 --> 00:26:52,400
provided to you by Dayazhai

579
00:26:52,400 --> 00:26:53,720
bear the same watermark.

580
00:26:53,960 --> 00:26:55,240
Let me explain here.

581
00:26:55,600 --> 00:26:57,640
The name on the watermark, Xuan Yongnian,

582
00:26:57,680 --> 00:27:00,040
is precisely the father of the plaintiff, Mr. Xuan Yan.

583
00:27:00,760 --> 00:27:01,640
Mr. Xuan Yongnian,

584
00:27:02,000 --> 00:27:04,440
an Intangible Cultural Heritage inheritor,

585
00:27:04,440 --> 00:27:07,520
stopped making paper a year and a half ago.

586
00:27:07,600 --> 00:27:11,600
Xuan paper bearing his name is a collector's edition,

587
00:27:12,520 --> 00:27:13,960
never circulated on the market.

588
00:27:13,960 --> 00:27:16,440
So we'd like Your Honor to note a detail.

589
00:27:16,640 --> 00:27:18,040
The plaintiff, Mr. Xuan Yan,

590
00:27:18,160 --> 00:27:21,120
used this special paper for all original drafts

591
00:27:21,320 --> 00:27:23,240
of the XuanBao Cultural Creative series.

592
00:27:23,560 --> 00:27:26,320
If the defendant's original design drafts

593
00:27:26,520 --> 00:27:29,040
also bear this exclusive Xuan family watermark,

594
00:27:29,240 --> 00:27:30,680
that fully proves

595
00:27:30,960 --> 00:27:31,960
that the patent application draft

596
00:27:32,040 --> 00:27:33,280
submitted by the defendant

597
00:27:33,520 --> 00:27:36,280
is Mr. Xuan Yan's original design draft.

598
00:27:36,280 --> 00:27:37,520
Well spoken this time.

599
00:27:41,880 --> 00:27:44,520
That inference doesn't hold up.

600
00:27:45,040 --> 00:27:47,240
The same paper doesn't sufficiently prove

601
00:27:47,240 --> 00:27:49,040
that the works on it belong to the same person.

602
00:27:49,840 --> 00:27:51,440
The Xuan family is a paper-making dynasty.

603
00:27:51,440 --> 00:27:53,320
The paper's quality is beyond doubt.

604
00:27:53,560 --> 00:27:54,720
Our designers,

605
00:27:55,000 --> 00:27:57,520
out of responsibility and respect for their work,

606
00:27:58,160 --> 00:27:59,840
also used the same paper.

607
00:28:00,200 --> 00:28:01,440
What's the problem with that?

608
00:28:02,760 --> 00:28:03,760
The key is, this paper

609
00:28:03,760 --> 00:28:05,560
has never been sold to the public.

610
00:28:05,560 --> 00:28:06,520
How can you prove that?

611
00:28:06,880 --> 00:28:08,320
Even if it wasn't sold publicly,

612
00:28:08,680 --> 00:28:12,880
was there ever a gift, exchange, or trade?

613
00:28:13,680 --> 00:28:14,960
And how do you prove

614
00:28:15,000 --> 00:28:16,120
that you got our paper?

615
00:28:16,200 --> 00:28:16,920
Your Honor,

616
00:28:17,280 --> 00:28:19,160
the plaintiff is muddying the waters.

617
00:28:19,440 --> 00:28:19,760
According to

618
00:28:19,760 --> 00:28:21,720
the Civil Procedure Law of the PRC,

619
00:28:21,720 --> 00:28:23,200
Article 67 clearly stipulates

620
00:28:23,200 --> 00:28:25,160
that parties are responsible for providing evidence

621
00:28:25,200 --> 00:28:26,760
for the claims they raise.

622
00:28:26,760 --> 00:28:27,800
In other words,

623
00:28:27,840 --> 00:28:31,040
if the watermark on the plaintiff's design draft

624
00:28:31,080 --> 00:28:32,760
is a one-of-a-kind item,

625
00:28:32,800 --> 00:28:34,440
and has not been sold publicly,

626
00:28:34,480 --> 00:28:37,920
the plaintiff should provide corresponding evidence.

627
00:28:38,240 --> 00:28:41,520
Otherwise, it shouldn't be admitted as evidence.

628
00:28:44,280 --> 00:28:45,200
Plaintiff, defendant,

629
00:28:45,760 --> 00:28:46,760
do either of you

630
00:28:47,280 --> 00:28:48,960
have any further evidence to submit?

631
00:28:52,320 --> 00:28:53,120
Anything else?

632
00:29:02,440 --> 00:29:03,440
Court is adjourned.

633
00:29:03,600 --> 00:29:04,600
The verdict will be announced shortly.

634
00:29:10,720 --> 00:29:11,760
The judgment is as follows.

635
00:29:12,000 --> 00:29:13,040
Please rise.

636
00:29:15,560 --> 00:29:16,480
This court holds that,

637
00:29:16,560 --> 00:29:16,880
pursuant to

638
00:29:16,880 --> 00:29:19,000
the Civil Procedure Law of the PRC,

639
00:29:19,000 --> 00:29:21,160
Article 67,

640
00:29:21,720 --> 00:29:24,520
the burden of proof in patent disputes

641
00:29:24,880 --> 00:29:27,440
lies with the party asserting the right.

642
00:29:28,000 --> 00:29:28,800
In this case,

643
00:29:29,040 --> 00:29:30,600
the plaintiff's evidence

644
00:29:30,760 --> 00:29:32,080
fails to substantiate their claim.

645
00:29:32,200 --> 00:29:33,960
Whereas the evidence submitted by the defendant

646
00:29:34,000 --> 00:29:36,240
is authentic, lawful, and relevant.

647
00:29:36,280 --> 00:29:38,840
All plaintiff's claims are dismissed.

648
00:29:42,760 --> 00:29:43,320
Mr. Xuan Yan.

649
00:29:44,600 --> 00:29:45,720
I'm sorry, Mr. Xuan.

650
00:29:45,720 --> 00:29:47,440
Um, here's what we'll do.

651
00:29:47,560 --> 00:29:49,120
Let's go back and think of something.

652
00:29:49,240 --> 00:29:50,560
We'll try to file an appeal ASAP.

653
00:29:50,560 --> 00:29:52,920
This way, during the second trial,

654
00:29:52,920 --> 00:29:53,600
we might get a turnaround.

655
00:29:53,600 --> 00:29:54,960
Like I'd hire you for the second trial?

656
00:29:55,040 --> 00:29:56,960
Didn't you say you were 100% certain?

657
00:29:57,040 --> 00:29:58,520
I was 100% certain originally.

658
00:29:58,520 --> 00:29:58,800
You...

659
00:29:58,800 --> 00:29:59,360
I just didn't expect...

660
00:29:59,360 --> 00:30:00,160
Enough, Wang Esq.

661
00:30:00,160 --> 00:30:01,520
Stop talking, just go back.

662
00:30:36,040 --> 00:30:37,640
I'm still worried, Lin Yiran.

663
00:30:38,280 --> 00:30:40,280
We don't have any new evidence this time.

664
00:30:40,520 --> 00:30:42,080
Going in like this, you'd...

665
00:30:42,600 --> 00:30:43,600
Don't worry.

666
00:30:44,400 --> 00:30:46,240
The lawyer Emma found for me

667
00:30:46,240 --> 00:30:48,720
is one of the top ones in Beijing.

668
00:30:48,760 --> 00:30:50,600
Whether it'll work out, we still need to meet and talk.

669
00:30:51,960 --> 00:30:52,800
Then hurry back as soon as you can.

670
00:30:52,800 --> 00:30:53,520
Remember,

671
00:30:53,520 --> 00:30:54,640
no matter the outcome,

672
00:30:54,640 --> 00:30:56,040
don't carry it all on your own.

673
00:30:56,120 --> 00:30:56,840
We're here with you.

674
00:30:56,840 --> 00:30:57,720
Got it.

675
00:30:57,760 --> 00:30:58,920
Okay, hurry on back now.

676
00:30:58,920 --> 00:30:59,720
I'll remember.

677
00:31:01,440 --> 00:31:02,280
Have a safe trip.

678
00:31:02,280 --> 00:31:04,080
I'm coming back, you know. Like I wouldn't.

679
00:31:04,080 --> 00:31:05,120
Hurry on back now.

680
00:31:05,120 --> 00:31:05,440
I'm off.

681
00:31:05,440 --> 00:31:06,160
I'll be waiting.

682
00:31:06,160 --> 00:31:06,560
I'm going.

683
00:31:06,560 --> 00:31:07,440
Text me if anything comes up.

684
00:31:07,440 --> 00:31:08,600
Got it. Bye.

685
00:31:24,960 --> 00:31:25,440
Get up.

686
00:31:26,400 --> 00:31:26,840
This...

687
00:31:27,480 --> 00:31:28,880
This furniture is expensive.

688
00:31:31,440 --> 00:31:33,000
Lin Yiran has already arrived in Beijing.

689
00:31:33,000 --> 00:31:34,080
She'll meet the lawyer right away.

690
00:31:34,200 --> 00:31:35,000
As for you,

691
00:31:35,080 --> 00:31:37,120
just stay put at my place.

692
00:31:37,200 --> 00:31:38,240
Wait for Lin Yiran.

693
00:31:38,240 --> 00:31:39,800
No, I still need to go check.

694
00:31:39,800 --> 00:31:40,600
Stay here.

695
00:31:40,600 --> 00:31:41,440
Stay at home.

696
00:31:41,760 --> 00:31:42,720
You can't go anywhere.

697
00:31:42,720 --> 00:31:43,680
Just stay right here.

698
00:31:44,280 --> 00:31:44,760
Also,

699
00:31:45,480 --> 00:31:46,760
Master's wife called me too.

700
00:31:46,760 --> 00:31:47,760
You can't go home either.

701
00:31:48,280 --> 00:31:50,680
What if Lin Yiran's lawyer doesn't work?

702
00:31:51,000 --> 00:31:52,560
Can I hide here at your place forever?

703
00:31:52,680 --> 00:31:54,680
The whole town is looking for you now.

704
00:31:54,680 --> 00:31:56,400
Desperate people turn into mad dogs.

705
00:31:56,400 --> 00:31:58,000
Barking and biting wildly.

706
00:31:58,000 --> 00:31:59,560
Then I need to go explain it to them.

707
00:31:59,560 --> 00:32:00,360
You stop right there!

708
00:32:01,560 --> 00:32:02,920
Don't... don't stop me.

709
00:32:04,120 --> 00:32:05,040
You're using all your strength on me.

710
00:32:05,040 --> 00:32:05,800
Stand still.

711
00:32:06,240 --> 00:32:07,000
Stay here.

712
00:32:08,840 --> 00:32:10,880
I told you, they're all furious right now.

713
00:32:11,240 --> 00:32:12,840
Can you please stop causing trouble?

714
00:32:12,840 --> 00:32:14,480
You want to be a hero,

715
00:32:14,680 --> 00:32:16,400
but can't you use your brain?

716
00:32:16,440 --> 00:32:17,320
My little ancestor.

717
00:32:31,120 --> 00:32:32,200
If you really want to leave,

718
00:32:32,840 --> 00:32:34,080
stay at my place one more night,

719
00:32:34,120 --> 00:32:35,080
then leave tomorrow.

720
00:32:48,240 --> 00:32:49,200
I recommend settling.

721
00:32:50,360 --> 00:32:52,400
These patents really are all ours.

722
00:32:52,400 --> 00:32:54,000
The other side registered them in bad faith.

723
00:32:54,000 --> 00:32:55,320
And they falsified documents.

724
00:32:55,400 --> 00:32:56,520
Yes, that's correct.

725
00:32:57,080 --> 00:32:58,960
But in court, evidence is what matters.

726
00:32:59,200 --> 00:33:01,240
You say they registered in bad faith and faked documents.

727
00:33:01,840 --> 00:33:04,000
But their chain of evidence is complete.

728
00:33:04,040 --> 00:33:05,800
Enough to support their claims.

729
00:33:07,040 --> 00:33:09,080
Unless you can find new evidence

730
00:33:09,160 --> 00:33:10,920
to break their chain of evidence.

731
00:33:12,240 --> 00:33:13,080
Fang Esq.

732
00:33:13,600 --> 00:33:15,000
You're the expert in this field.

733
00:33:15,360 --> 00:33:18,600
Is there any chance of overturning the verdict?

734
00:33:19,920 --> 00:33:21,440
As things stand, there's no chance.

735
00:33:22,800 --> 00:33:25,360
Settling is the best way to cut losses.

736
00:33:25,600 --> 00:33:26,400
Of course,

737
00:33:26,400 --> 00:33:27,560
this outcome, in your eyes,

738
00:33:27,560 --> 00:33:29,360
may be hard to accept.

739
00:33:29,520 --> 00:33:30,800
But to me, it's quite normal.

740
00:33:32,040 --> 00:33:32,840
Justice, you see,

741
00:33:33,000 --> 00:33:35,560
never fails to arrive, but it may be late.

742
00:33:35,920 --> 00:33:36,680
And how many people

743
00:33:36,680 --> 00:33:38,520
have died waiting for late justice?

744
00:33:38,920 --> 00:33:40,520
Using laws and regulations in advance

745
00:33:40,520 --> 00:33:42,000
to protect your rights

746
00:33:42,000 --> 00:33:43,200
is incredibly important.

747
00:33:46,120 --> 00:33:47,000
Thank you.

748
00:33:48,920 --> 00:33:49,720
Brother Min,

749
00:33:50,160 --> 00:33:52,080
even the Beijing lawyer's said this.

750
00:33:52,240 --> 00:33:54,120
Is there really no way out this time?

751
00:33:54,720 --> 00:33:56,480
Right, what are we supposed to do?

752
00:33:56,480 --> 00:33:57,800
Isn't this completely over?

753
00:33:57,920 --> 00:33:58,720
Chairman,

754
00:33:58,800 --> 00:34:00,920
you and Xuan Yan started this together.

755
00:34:00,920 --> 00:34:02,280
You've got to think of something.

756
00:34:02,320 --> 00:34:03,280
With no income coming in,

757
00:34:03,480 --> 00:34:04,800
I can't even pay the interest.

758
00:34:04,800 --> 00:34:07,120
My factory's about to shut down.

759
00:34:08,000 --> 00:34:09,520
Brother Min, you're the chairman.

760
00:34:09,560 --> 00:34:10,320
No matter what,

761
00:34:10,320 --> 00:34:11,239
you've got to tell us something.

762
00:34:11,960 --> 00:34:12,800
Start over.

763
00:34:13,719 --> 00:34:14,600
Start over?

764
00:34:15,120 --> 00:34:16,480
How are we supposed to start over?

765
00:34:16,480 --> 00:34:17,000
What about my interest?

766
00:34:17,000 --> 00:34:18,440
Things have come to this point.

767
00:34:19,159 --> 00:34:20,000
No matter how hard,

768
00:34:20,080 --> 00:34:21,800
we can't just surrender, right?

769
00:34:21,800 --> 00:34:22,560
That's true.

770
00:34:22,920 --> 00:34:24,719
XuanBao got so popular,

771
00:34:25,239 --> 00:34:27,080
and wasn't it Xuan Yan who designed it?

772
00:34:27,560 --> 00:34:28,760
As long as Xuan Yan's around,

773
00:34:28,920 --> 00:34:31,560
he can design a Ren-Bao,

774
00:34:31,960 --> 00:34:34,239
a Song-Bao, a Guo-Bao,

775
00:34:34,520 --> 00:34:36,600
and even a Fang-Bao, right?

776
00:34:37,920 --> 00:34:39,760
Sooner or later, we'll crush Dayazhai.

777
00:34:39,960 --> 00:34:40,520
Absolutely.

778
00:34:40,520 --> 00:34:41,520
He's got a point.

779
00:34:41,560 --> 00:34:43,320
Xuan Yan's the largest shareholder.

780
00:34:43,320 --> 00:34:44,800
Why hasn't he shown his face?

781
00:34:44,800 --> 00:34:46,040
Either way, we deserve an explanation.

782
00:34:46,520 --> 00:34:47,719
You've got to call him over.

783
00:34:47,719 --> 00:34:49,159
Give us an explanation.

784
00:34:49,159 --> 00:34:50,800
It's not that Xuan Yan won't show up.

785
00:34:50,840 --> 00:34:52,280
I don't dare let him come.

786
00:34:52,719 --> 00:34:53,760
Look at all of you,

787
00:34:54,239 --> 00:34:55,040
every one of you losing your cool.

788
00:34:55,040 --> 00:34:56,120
Especially someone like you.

789
00:34:56,120 --> 00:34:57,280
What if you go and hit him again?

790
00:34:57,280 --> 00:34:57,760
No, no.

791
00:34:57,760 --> 00:34:58,360
Right?

792
00:34:58,360 --> 00:34:59,000
I wouldn't.

793
00:34:59,760 --> 00:35:00,760
I wouldn't, I wouldn't.

794
00:35:00,760 --> 00:35:01,520
Old Xiao, Old Xiao.

795
00:35:02,400 --> 00:35:04,440
Look at what you just said.

796
00:35:04,680 --> 00:35:06,520
You can't speak for Xuan Yan.

797
00:35:06,520 --> 00:35:07,240
Right?

798
00:35:07,480 --> 00:35:08,720
This Cultural Creative stuff,

799
00:35:08,720 --> 00:35:10,840
not one of us here understands it.

800
00:35:10,840 --> 00:35:11,760
Right, we don't get it.

801
00:35:11,760 --> 00:35:12,720
How about this?

802
00:35:13,000 --> 00:35:15,280
Bring him over to explain it to us.

803
00:35:15,400 --> 00:35:17,080
Then we can all discuss it together.

804
00:35:17,080 --> 00:35:17,920
Right?

805
00:35:18,000 --> 00:35:19,720
Even if we're starting over,

806
00:35:19,720 --> 00:35:20,480
we should at least hear

807
00:35:20,480 --> 00:35:22,000
what Xuan Yan's actually thinking, right?

808
00:35:22,000 --> 00:35:22,720
Exactly, right.

809
00:35:22,720 --> 00:35:24,200
Call him, give him a call.

810
00:35:24,200 --> 00:35:25,000
Give him a call.

811
00:35:25,200 --> 00:35:26,600
Yeah, yeah, you give him a call.

812
00:35:29,320 --> 00:35:30,600
I can call him over, sure.

813
00:35:30,840 --> 00:35:31,920
But let's agree in advance.

814
00:35:31,920 --> 00:35:32,920
No one loses their temper.

815
00:35:32,920 --> 00:35:34,000
We talk things out calmly.

816
00:35:34,840 --> 00:35:35,720
We swear, we swear.

817
00:35:35,720 --> 00:35:36,320
Absolutely.

818
00:35:36,320 --> 00:35:37,160
Don't worry.

819
00:35:40,360 --> 00:35:41,080
It's Xuan Yan.

820
00:36:01,360 --> 00:36:02,760
He didn't sleep at all last night.

821
00:36:02,800 --> 00:36:04,000
He's probably sleeping now.

822
00:36:04,160 --> 00:36:05,400
Tell you what, I'll go wake him up.

823
00:36:06,200 --> 00:36:09,480
Worst case, we start over from scratch.

824
00:36:09,920 --> 00:36:10,640
Xuan Yan!

825
00:36:11,560 --> 00:36:12,240
Xuan Yan!

826
00:36:13,920 --> 00:36:15,000
Playing hide-and-seek with me?

827
00:36:16,200 --> 00:36:18,680
There's a turnaround!

828
00:36:20,600 --> 00:36:21,280
Xuan Yan!

829
00:36:21,720 --> 00:36:24,040
We're starting completely fresh!

830
00:36:25,480 --> 00:36:26,160
Xuan Yan!

831
00:36:26,880 --> 00:36:27,560
Xuan Yan!

832
00:36:37,000 --> 00:36:37,880
His phone's off.

833
00:36:40,280 --> 00:36:41,800
The sky's already gotten dark.

834
00:36:41,960 --> 00:36:43,480
When is he coming back?

835
00:36:54,800 --> 00:36:55,560
Xuan Yan's here!

836
00:36:55,840 --> 00:36:56,680
He's here, he's here!

837
00:36:56,920 --> 00:36:58,360
Here he is, here he is!

838
00:36:59,000 --> 00:37:00,200
The chairman's car is back.

839
00:37:00,200 --> 00:37:00,920
Chairman Xiao is back!

840
00:37:00,920 --> 00:37:01,320
He's back!

841
00:37:01,920 --> 00:37:02,920
Finally back!

842
00:37:04,560 --> 00:37:05,480
Finally back!

843
00:37:05,680 --> 00:37:06,480
Chairman.

844
00:37:13,200 --> 00:37:14,000
Where's Xuan Yan?

845
00:37:15,000 --> 00:37:15,680
Where is he?

846
00:37:15,680 --> 00:37:16,440
Where, where is he?

847
00:37:16,440 --> 00:37:17,160
He ran off.

848
00:37:17,440 --> 00:37:18,640
Where, where is he?

849
00:37:19,120 --> 00:37:20,440
I couldn't find Xuan Yan.

850
00:37:20,520 --> 00:37:21,600
Did he run off?

851
00:37:21,760 --> 00:37:23,520
He didn't run. How could he run?

852
00:37:23,520 --> 00:37:24,880
No, if he didn't run, where is he?

853
00:37:24,880 --> 00:37:25,880
Right, where did he go?

854
00:37:25,880 --> 00:37:26,480
Exactly.

855
00:37:26,480 --> 00:37:28,080
I don't know. I can't reach him.

856
00:37:28,560 --> 00:37:29,920
Then he's gone, plain and simple.

857
00:37:29,920 --> 00:37:31,000
Tell us the truth.

858
00:37:31,080 --> 00:37:33,360
You're treating us like three-year-olds!

859
00:37:33,480 --> 00:37:35,320
You've been fooling us from the start!

860
00:37:35,360 --> 00:37:37,040
You've deceived us enough already!

861
00:37:37,040 --> 00:37:37,920
I already swore to you.

862
00:37:37,920 --> 00:37:39,320
I said I wouldn't lose my temper.

863
00:37:39,320 --> 00:37:39,880
Enough, enough.

864
00:37:39,880 --> 00:37:41,160
We just want to hear the truth now.

865
00:37:41,160 --> 00:37:42,160
What I'm saying is the truth.

866
00:37:42,160 --> 00:37:42,960
I'm not lying to you.

867
00:37:42,960 --> 00:37:44,520
Why would I ever lie to you?

868
00:37:44,640 --> 00:37:46,160
We're done for, we're done for!

869
00:37:46,560 --> 00:37:48,600
He ran off, what the hell can we do now?

870
00:37:48,720 --> 00:37:50,640
Everyone go home and call it a night.

871
00:37:50,640 --> 00:37:52,040
Let's go.

872
00:37:52,040 --> 00:37:52,800
Jiye.

873
00:37:53,520 --> 00:37:54,920
I said something was off.

874
00:37:54,920 --> 00:37:55,360
You all know it.

875
00:37:56,160 --> 00:37:56,680
No, you...

876
00:37:56,680 --> 00:37:58,040
Everyone go home and wait for news.

877
00:37:58,320 --> 00:37:59,520
Liars! They're all liars!

878
00:37:59,920 --> 00:38:00,160
Let's go.

879
00:38:00,160 --> 00:38:01,200
Go home and wait for news.

880
00:38:05,040 --> 00:38:05,960
Old Xiao.

881
00:38:06,440 --> 00:38:10,200
I really hope you're not lying to us this time.

882
00:38:12,200 --> 00:38:13,000
Guangping.

883
00:38:13,840 --> 00:38:15,800
You know what kind of man Brother Min is.

884
00:38:23,880 --> 00:38:25,960
Brother Min, don't be anxious.

885
00:38:26,280 --> 00:38:28,120
Wait a bit longer, there'll be a way.

886
00:38:30,840 --> 00:38:33,000
Brother Min, take it easy.

887
00:38:33,480 --> 00:38:34,600
Xuan Yan is nowhere to be found.

888
00:38:34,600 --> 00:38:36,120
You still have me, Erhu.

889
00:38:46,440 --> 00:38:47,160
Let's go.

890
00:38:47,160 --> 00:38:48,400
Old Song, have you gone mad?

891
00:38:48,720 --> 00:38:50,360
Don't you want to live?

892
00:38:55,840 --> 00:38:56,480
Move aside, move aside.

893
00:38:56,880 --> 00:38:58,000
How am I supposed to go on?

894
00:38:58,000 --> 00:38:59,680
What's going on? Is the fire out?

895
00:39:00,080 --> 00:39:00,840
Don't worry, relax.

896
00:39:00,840 --> 00:39:01,920
It's all out, all out.

897
00:39:02,720 --> 00:39:04,520
What's the matter with you two?

898
00:39:04,720 --> 00:39:06,320
How could you burn down your own factory?

899
00:39:06,440 --> 00:39:07,920
I don't want to live anymore.

900
00:39:07,920 --> 00:39:09,800
Our family's factory is gone.

901
00:39:10,000 --> 00:39:12,720
The town and the association are finding a solution.

902
00:39:12,800 --> 00:39:14,600
We haven't hit a dead end yet.

903
00:39:14,640 --> 00:39:16,040
Even if we did hit a dead end,

904
00:39:16,080 --> 00:39:17,680
we'd still fight our way through for everyone.

905
00:39:17,800 --> 00:39:19,680
Chairman Xiao, Xuan Yan, and us

906
00:39:19,920 --> 00:39:21,640
will definitely give you all an answer.

907
00:39:22,320 --> 00:39:23,080
Old Song.

908
00:39:23,280 --> 00:39:24,920
Don't ever do this again, you hear me?

909
00:39:25,280 --> 00:39:26,000
You hear me?

910
00:39:26,080 --> 00:39:27,160
No more foolish acts.

911
00:39:27,280 --> 00:39:28,920
All our money is gone.

912
00:39:28,920 --> 00:39:30,560
And we still owe a lot of debt.

913
00:39:30,560 --> 00:39:32,880
How are we supposed to live?

914
00:39:34,400 --> 00:39:35,040
You can't think that way.

915
00:39:35,560 --> 00:39:36,880
We're working on a solution.

916
00:39:36,880 --> 00:39:37,880
Working on it.

917
00:39:49,160 --> 00:39:50,560
Call me if you find any places for rent.

918
00:39:51,000 --> 00:39:51,640
Thanks for your trouble.

919
00:39:51,640 --> 00:39:52,200
Sure.

920
00:39:52,200 --> 00:39:53,000
Take care.

921
00:40:15,880 --> 00:40:16,800
He's still not back yet.

922
00:40:21,120 --> 00:40:23,680
Xuan Yan poured his heart into XuanBao.

923
00:40:23,720 --> 00:40:25,640
Then suddenly the patent belongs to someone else.

924
00:40:27,320 --> 00:40:28,120
Xiaomin.

925
00:40:28,480 --> 00:40:29,840
You don't think something's happened to him, do you?

926
00:40:30,240 --> 00:40:31,720
What could possibly happen to him?

927
00:40:32,640 --> 00:40:33,640
That guy...

928
00:40:34,520 --> 00:40:37,520
Even at the end of the world, he'd think

929
00:40:37,880 --> 00:40:40,320
about how to put it all back together.

930
00:40:40,440 --> 00:40:42,240
He's not the type to fall apart.

931
00:40:44,040 --> 00:40:45,280
Life is like ink.

932
00:40:46,560 --> 00:40:47,680
Sometimes bold, sometimes faint.

933
00:40:48,440 --> 00:40:49,880
Ever-shifting shades are the norm.

934
00:40:50,360 --> 00:40:53,120
But Paper lives a thousand years relies on resilience.

935
00:40:53,360 --> 00:40:54,440
It's the same with people.

936
00:40:55,000 --> 00:40:57,040
Pain, hardship, difficulty...

937
00:40:57,240 --> 00:40:59,120
Every hurdle is hard, but can be overcome

938
00:40:59,360 --> 00:41:00,080
But only through this

939
00:41:00,080 --> 00:41:02,120
can our hearts grow truly stronger.

940
00:41:02,440 --> 00:41:03,840
That's what my master taught me.

941
00:41:07,480 --> 00:41:08,280
With Xuan Yan gone,

942
00:41:08,520 --> 00:41:10,240
we can't move forward with the work.

943
00:41:10,960 --> 00:41:12,600
So the key to solving this

944
00:41:12,600 --> 00:41:13,400
is still him.

945
00:41:14,120 --> 00:41:15,680
But until he comes back,

946
00:41:15,680 --> 00:41:16,920
we can't lose our heads.

947
00:41:17,400 --> 00:41:18,440
We have to hold it together.

948
00:41:22,400 --> 00:41:24,200
Right, we have to hold on.

949
00:41:26,840 --> 00:41:28,000
I mean, that jerk...

950
00:41:28,000 --> 00:41:29,800
He said he'd shield me from the storm.

951
00:41:30,000 --> 00:41:31,560
Then trouble hits and he vanishes first.

952
00:41:34,680 --> 00:41:35,480
Come on.

953
00:41:35,600 --> 00:41:37,360
He wouldn't just abandon us.

954
00:41:37,480 --> 00:41:39,120
Let's go grab some food.

955
00:41:39,520 --> 00:41:41,600
Eat well, then work hard.

956
00:42:03,280 --> 00:42:05,800
Ms. Xin, hope I'm not interrupting.

957
00:42:07,080 --> 00:42:08,320
Nothing major, really.

958
00:42:08,560 --> 00:42:12,120
It's just, the chairman again.

959
00:42:12,280 --> 00:42:14,640
He's hoping you can sign the contract soon.

960
00:42:14,840 --> 00:42:16,320
Please don't put me in a tough spot.

961
00:42:18,800 --> 00:42:20,360
I've got a few things on my plate.

962
00:42:20,960 --> 00:42:21,840
Once I've signed,

963
00:42:21,840 --> 00:42:23,480
I'll have Yuqing bring it over to you.

964
00:42:31,000 --> 00:42:33,840
You know, we've worked together for quite a while.

965
00:42:34,320 --> 00:42:37,520
There's something heartfelt I'd like to say.

966
00:42:37,840 --> 00:42:39,640
Not sure if I should say it or not.

967
00:42:40,920 --> 00:42:41,640
Go ahead.

968
00:42:44,000 --> 00:42:46,560
The truth is, to Peach Blossom Town,

969
00:42:46,960 --> 00:42:48,520
you and I are both outsiders.

970
00:42:49,200 --> 00:42:51,400
We came to get a piece of the pie.

971
00:42:51,400 --> 00:42:52,920
If we can, we stick around a few more years.

972
00:42:53,400 --> 00:42:54,520
If we can't get our share,

973
00:42:55,120 --> 00:42:56,040
we turn around and leave.

974
00:42:56,520 --> 00:42:58,400
We came here just to make some money.
